# Upstream binary — `gosu` in `postgres:18-alpine`
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Reviewed 2026-05-06 — these are Go stdlib + jsonparser CVEs in the
# `gosu` binary shipped at `/usr/local/bin/gosu` by the upstream
# postgres image. `gosu` is invoked exactly once by postgres' entrypoint
# to drop privileges from root before exec'ing postgres itself; it does
# not open network sockets, parse untrusted input, or process JSON in
# our usage path. The vulnerable Go stdlib code paths
# (net/http parsing, crypto/x509, encoding/* fuzzing) are not reachable
# from gosu's `setgid()/setuid()/exec()` flow. We cannot rebuild gosu
# from this repo (it's a pre-compiled binary inherited from upstream);
# the fix lands when `postgres:18-alpine` rebuilds against a patched
# Go toolchain. Re-eval 2026-Q3.
